.
.

#unboundbybeads 

a sphere that unbounds as a reflection of them,
every bead stitch ties them with their surrounding,
a stitch that shapes them in the circular mould,
a stitch that bonds every daughter and mother,
the glass beads reflects the stories
of their hands a transition,
a journey of embracing expression,
a craft stitched bead by bead
of stories that were inside,
voices that were inside of the sphere
they lived in in the spheres they crafted.

latestPosts.caption:
The bead craft tradition of Kutch and Kathiawar represents a distinctly gendered craft practice, exclusively practiced by women across both the regions. This specialized knowledge, with techniques, patterns, and artistic sensibilities was passed down from mother to her daughter through generations.
